---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Security — Telepathine.ai',
  description: 'Isolation you can verify. Row-Level Security with FORCE policies, project-scoped data, BYOK encryption, and a published postmortem of our cross-project isolation fix.',
  url: 'https://telepathine.ai/security',
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'ArtemisAI',
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Security — Telepathine.ai"
  description="Isolation you can verify. Row-Level Security, project-scoped data, BYOK encryption, and a published postmortem of our cross-project isolation fix."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <!-- ====== HEADER ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 pb-8 pt-24 sm:px-6 sm:pt-32 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <h1>Isolation you can verify</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Your agent memory contains your decisions, your architecture, your trade-offs. It should never leak to another tenant — and you should be able to prove it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== LEAK-01 POSTMORTEM ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line);">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <span class="layer-label">Incident Postmortem</span>
      <h2 class="mt-4">We learned data isolation the hard way</h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-copy);">
        In May 2026, we discovered that a default project fallback in our context injection path caused
        <strong style="color: var(--text);">6,500+ observations from 5 different projects</strong>
        to share a single namespace called <code class="tag-mono">"default"</code>. When a plugin could not derive
        a project name from the current working directory, it silently fell back to this generic scope — mixing
        observations from unrelated codebases into one shared pool.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-copy);">
        This was not a theoretical risk. It was real data from real projects — architectural decisions, debugging
        trails, session summaries — all queryable by any tenant whose plugin hit the same fallback path.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-lg border p-6" style="background: var(--bg-card); border-color: var(--line-strong);">
        <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--accent);">What we did</h3>
        <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-copy);">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="step-circle flex-shrink-0">1</span>
            <div>
              <strong style="color: var(--text);">Permanently removed the fallback.</strong>
              The <code class="tag-mono">"default"</code> project name is now forbidden in context injection paths.
              When a plugin cannot derive a project name, it returns zero results — not a leak from another project.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="step-circle flex-shrink-0">2</span>
            <div>
              <strong style="color: var(--text);">Backfilled all affected data.</strong>
              Every observation previously stored under <code class="tag-mono">"default"</code> was migrated to its
              correct project namespace — on both the primary database and the secondary cloud replica.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="step-circle flex-shrink-0">3</span>
            <div>
              <strong style="color: var(--text);">Wrote regression tests.</strong>
              Guard tests in <code class="tag-mono">leak01-guard.test.ts</code> run in CI on every push.
              The standing instruction: <em style="color: var(--accent);">"If this test fails, DO NOT change the test. Fix the installer code."</em>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="step-circle flex-shrink-0">4</span>
            <div>
              <strong style="color: var(--text);">Documented the fix publicly.</strong>
              Most companies hide incidents. We published ours — because a test you can read is worth
              more than a claim you cannot verify.
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== ISOLATION VERIFICATION ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <span class="layer-label">Verify It Yourself</span>
      <h2 class="mt-4">Isolation verification demo</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-xl text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">
        No competitor offers an API endpoint you can hit to verify project isolation. We do. Run this curl command against your own project:
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 code-terminal" style="max-width: 640px;">
        <div class="code-terminal-bar">
          <span class="code-terminal-dot code-terminal-dot-red"></span>
          <span class="code-terminal-dot code-terminal-dot-yellow"></span>
          <span class="code-terminal-dot code-terminal-dot-green"></span>
          <span class="ml-4 font-mono text-[10px]" style="color: var(--text-muted);">terminal</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-terminal-body">
          <pre style="white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-all;"><span class="syn-cmt"># Verify your project returns only its own observations</span>
<span class="syn-kw">$</span> curl -s https://api.telepathine.ai/v1/context/inject \
  -G -d <span class="syn-str">"projects=your-project"</span> -d <span class="syn-str">"limit=5"</span> \
  -H <span class="syn-str">"Authorization: Bearer $TELEPATHINE_API_KEY"</span>

<span class="syn-cmt"># Returns ONLY your-project's observations</span>
<span class="syn-cmt"># Never includes "default" scope</span>
<span class="syn-cmt"># Zero observations for unknown projects</span></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-lg border p-4" style="background: var(--bg-card); border-color: var(--line-strong);">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--accent-secondary);">Test 1</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Query your own project — get only your data back.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border p-4" style="background: var(--bg-card); border-color: var(--line-strong);">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--accent-secondary);">Test 2</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Query an unknown project name — get zero observations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border p-4" style="background: var(--bg-card); border-color: var(--line-strong);">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--accent-secondary);">Test 3</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Never see a "default" fallback scope in any response.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== ISOLATION ARCHITECTURE ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line);">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <span class="layer-label">Architecture</span>
      <h2 class="mt-4">How isolation works</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="surface-card p-6">
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text);">Row-Level Security with FORCE policies</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Every database table uses PostgreSQL Row-Level Security with <code class="tag-mono">FORCE</code> policies. Tenant isolation is enforced at the database layer — not the application layer. Even a misconfigured API endpoint cannot retrieve data from another tenant because the database rejects the query before it returns rows.</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">API keys carry tenant context. Read, write, and admin scopes limit what each key can do. Project visibility settings (private, tenant, shared) give fine-grained control within your organization.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface-card p-6">
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text);">Project-scoped queries</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Every observation, session, and context injection is scoped to a specific project. Queries never cross project boundaries — not by default, not by accident, not by fallback. When a project has no data, you get zero results — not a leak from another project's history.</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Project names are derived from Git remote, config file, or CWD basename. There is no generic fallback scope. The LEAK-01 postmortem above explains why.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== BYOK + ENCRYPTION ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <span class="layer-label">Encryption</span>
      <h2 class="mt-4">Your keys, your models</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="surface-card p-6">
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text);">BYOK on every tier</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">On every plan — including the free tier — you can configure your own LLM and embedding provider keys. OpenAI, Anthropic, or any compatible endpoint. Your AI provider keys are encrypted at rest and never shared between tenants or used for any purpose other than your own Morpheus pipeline and embedding operations.</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">We never train on your data. We never use your AI keys for anyone else's requests.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface-card p-6">
          <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text);">API key security</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">API keys are hashed at rest using SHA-256. Keys are never stored in plaintext and never appear in hook commands, logs, or error messages. The <code class="tag-mono">~/.agent-memory/env</code> file provides secure key management with file-system permissions.</p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Full REST API export is available at any time. No vendor lock-in, no data hostage situation. Your memory travels with you.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 code-terminal">
            <div class="code-terminal-bar">
              <span class="code-terminal-dot code-terminal-dot-red"></span>
              <span class="code-terminal-dot code-terminal-dot-yellow"></span>
              <span class="code-terminal-dot code-terminal-dot-green"></span>
              <span class="ml-4 font-mono text-[10px]" style="color: var(--text-muted);">terminal</span>
            </div>
            <div class="code-terminal-body">
              <pre style="white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-all;"><span class="syn-cmt"># Export all observations for a project</span>
<span class="syn-kw">$</span> curl https://api.telepathine.ai/v1/observations \
  -H <span class="syn-str">"Authorization: Bearer $TELEPATHINE_API_KEY"</span> \
  -G -d <span class="syn-str">"project=my-project&limit=10000"</span> \
  > export.json</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== COMPLIANCE ROADMAP ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line);">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <span class="layer-label">Compliance</span>
      <h2 class="mt-4">Compliance roadmap</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-xl text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Honest status, not marketing claims. In progress does not mean compliant. Partial does not mean certified.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);">
              <th class="pb-3 pr-4 text-left text-xs" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Standard</th>
              <th class="pb-3 px-4 text-center text-xs" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Status</th>
              <th class="pb-3 pl-4 text-left text-xs" style="color: var(--text-muted);">What to expect</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">RLS (FORCE policies)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 text-center"><span class="badge-stable rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium">Live</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Every table, FORCE policies. Database-layer enforcement.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">BYOK</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 text-center"><span class="badge-stable rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium">Live</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Your keys, your models. Free on all tiers.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">Export (full REST API)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 text-center"><span class="badge-stable rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium">Live</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Full REST API, no lock-in. Export any time.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">SOC 2 Type I</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 text-center"><span class="badge-beta rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium">In progress</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Targeting Q3 2026. Not yet certified.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">SOC 2 Type II</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 text-center"><span class="badge-alpha rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium">Planned</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Targeting Q3 2027. Dependent on Type I completion.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">GDPR</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 text-center"><span class="badge-alpha rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium">Partial</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Export API supports right-to-access. Right-to-erasure endpoint and DPA in progress. Not yet compliant.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">HIPAA</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 text-center"><span class="rounded-full border px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium" style="border-color: var(--line); color: var(--text-muted);">N/A</span></td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">We do not process Protected Health Information. HIPAA does not apply.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== TRUST LANGUAGE ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <span class="layer-label">Language</span>
      <h2 class="mt-4">What we say and why</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-xl text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Specific, verifiable language over marketing abstraction. If we cannot prove it, we do not claim it.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);">
              <th class="pb-3 pr-4 text-left text-xs" style="color: var(--accent-secondary);">We say</th>
              <th class="pb-3 pl-4 text-left text-xs" style="color: #ef4444;">We never say</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Row-Level Security with FORCE policies</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4" style="color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.5; text-decoration: line-through;">Enterprise-grade security</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Per-tenant, per-project isolation</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4" style="color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.5; text-decoration: line-through;">Data is kept safe</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">API keys hashed at rest (SHA-256)</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4" style="color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.5; text-decoration: line-through;">Military-grade encryption</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">No default fallback — zero results for unknown projects</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4" style="color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.5; text-decoration: line-through;">We take isolation seriously</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Regression tests prevent reintroduction</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4" style="color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.5; text-decoration: line-through;">This will never happen again</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">BYOK — your keys, your models</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4" style="color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.5; text-decoration: line-through;">We protect your data</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Full REST API, no lock-in</td>
              <td class="py-3 pl-4" style="color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.5; text-decoration: line-through;">Seamless integration</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== SECURITY PRINCIPLES ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line);">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <span class="layer-label">Principles</span>
      <h2 class="mt-4">Security principles</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="step-circle">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">Isolation by default</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Data is scoped to your tenant and project. There is no "see everything" mode. Zero results for a new project is correct behavior — not a bug to work around with fallback scopes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="step-circle">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">Verify, don't trust</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Regression tests guard against known isolation failures. When we find a leak, we fix it, backfill affected data, and write a test that catches a recurrence. Guard tests run in CI on every push.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="step-circle">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">Transparency over silence</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">When we find a security issue, we document it. We published the details of our cross-project isolation fix because transparency builds trust — and because a test you can read is worth more than a claim you cannot verify.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="step-circle">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold" style="color: var(--text);">Your keys, your models</h3>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">BYOK on every tier. We never use your AI provider keys for anything other than your own requests. We never train on your data. Your LLM calls, your embeddings, your Morpheus summaries — all processed with keys you control.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== RESPONSIBLE DISCLOSURE ====== -->
  <section class="content-layer px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--line-subtle);">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <h2>Report a vulnerability</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-xl text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Found a security issue? We want to hear about it — and we will credit responsible disclosures.</p>
      <div class="mt-6 rounded-lg border p-6" style="background: var(--bg-card); border-color: var(--line-strong);">
        <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Email</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text);">
              <a href="mailto:security@telepathine.ai" class="content-link">security@telepathine.ai</a>
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--text-muted);">PGP</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Available on request. Encrypt sensitive reports before sending.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Response time</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-copy);">Within 48 hours.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--text-muted);">Policy</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--text-copy);">We credit responsible disclosures. We do not pursue legal action against good-faith researchers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
